The rape of Ganymede, has its foundation in the following circumstances in history: Tros, king of Troy, having been successful against his neighbours, sent his son into Lydia, to offer sacrifices in the Temple of Jupiter; but this not being known to Tantalus, who had the eagle in his ensign, he caused Ganymede and his people to be arrested in the Temple, and thrown into prison, taking them for spieS. The story of his being ap- pointed Cup-bearer to the Gods, arose *from his being employed in* that ’ station in the court of Lydia. The poets liave' placed him in the Heavens, where he forms the sign Aquarius. The rape of Ganymede was the occa- sion of that of Helen by Paris, the great grandson of Tros, who made this repr-isal on Menelaus, king of Lacedemon‚ the great grandson of the ravisher of Ganymede. Agamemnon made use of this event to engage the Greeks and Trojans in the war so fatal to the latter.
